    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A dashboard-style, single-page application with sticky top navigation to allow non-linear exploration of the marketing plan. The structure is thematic (Threat, Strategy, Campaign, Budget/KPIs) rather than mirroring the report's linear format. This design choice makes the complex information more digestible and allows users to quickly access sections of interest. Key interactions include tabbed content for the campaign details, accordions for industry-specific risks, and an interactive chart for the budget, all designed to reduce cognitive load and improve user engagement. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: Budget Allocation -> Goal: Compare -> Viz: Donut Chart -> Interaction: Hover tooltips -> Justification: Provides a quick, visual summary of financial distribution. -> Library: Chart.js.
        - Report Info: Multi-Channel Program -> Goal: Organize -> Viz: Tabbed Interface -> Interaction: Click to switch content -> Justification: Segments the detailed campaign tactics into manageable sections. -> Library: Vanilla JS.
        - Report Info: Industry Vulnerabilities -> Goal: Organize/Compare -> Viz: Accordion -> Interaction: Click to expand/collapse -> Justification: Prevents a long wall of text, allowing users to focus on relevant industries. -> Library: Vanilla JS.
        - Report Info: Ethical Simulation Phases -> Goal: Show Process -> Viz: HTML/CSS Timeline -> Interaction: Hover highlights -> Justification: Visually communicates the sequence of the creative campaign core. -> Library: HTML/Tailwind.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
